.\" get-chassis.1 - manpage for get-chassis
.TH GET\-CHASSIS 1 "2026-03-31" "1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
get\-chassis \- return chassis type of current machine
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B get\-chassis
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RI [ TYPE ]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B get\-chassis
prints the chassis type of the current machine (e.g.,
.IR laptop ,
.IR desktop ,
.IR tablet ).
.PP
If one or more
.I TYPE
arguments are given,
.B get\-chassis
exits 0 if the current chassis matches any of them, or exits 1 otherwise.
Comparison is case\-insensitive.
.PP
Detection tries
.BR hostnamectl (1)
first, then falls back to the SMBIOS chassis_type code in
.IR /sys/class/dmi/id/chassis_type .
.PP
.B get\-chassis
can also be sourced as a Bash library, which exports the
.B get_chassis
function into the calling shell.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help and exit.
.SH VALID CHASSIS TYPES
.TS
l l.
1	other
2	unknown
3	desktop
4	low\-profile\-desktop
5	pizza\-box
6	mini\-tower
7	tower
8	portable
9	laptop
10	notebook
11	hand\-held
12	docking\-station
13	all\-in\-one
14	sub\-notebook
15	space\-saving
16	lunch\-box
17	main\-server\-chassis
18	expansion\-chassis
19	sub\-chassis
20	bus\-expansion\-chassis
21	peripheral\-chassis
22	raid\-chassis
23	rack\-mount\-chassis
24	sealed\-case\-pc
25	multi\-system\-chassis
26	compact\-pci
27	advanced\-tca
28	blade
29	blade\-enclosure
30	tablet
31	convertible
32	detachable
33	iot\-gateway
34	embedded\-pc
35	mini\-pc
36	stick\-pc
.TE
.PP
These correspond to SMBIOS specification chassis type codes from
.IR /sys/class/dmi/id/chassis_type .
.SH EXAMPLES
Print the chassis type:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ get\-chassis
laptop
.fi
.RE
.PP
Test against one or more types:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ get\-chassis laptop notebook && echo "Portable"
Portable
.fi
.RE
.PP
Use as a conditional in a script:
.PP
.RS
.nf
if get\-chassis desktop mini\-tower tower; then
  echo "This is a desktop system"
fi
.fi
.RE
.PP
Source as a library:
.PP
.RS
.nf
source get\-chassis
get_chassis laptop && echo "Running on a laptop"
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Chassis type detected (no arguments), or a match was found (with arguments).
.TP
.B 1
No match found (with arguments), or unknown option given.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
No environment variables are used.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /sys/class/dmi/id/chassis_type
SMBIOS chassis type code (fallback detection).
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.BR jq (1)
Used to parse hostnamectl JSON output. Optional \(em falls back to SMBIOS
if unavailable.
.TP
.BR hostnamectl (1)
Primary detection method (requires systemd 246+). Optional \(em falls back
to SMBIOS if unavailable.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.TP
.B Bash 4.4+
Uses
.IR inherit_errexit ,
.IR "${var,,}" " lowercase expansion, and"
.IR "${var@Q}" " quoting transform."
.TP
.B Linux
Requires either systemd or DMI/SMBIOS support.
.SH BUGS
On systems without both systemd and DMI (e.g., ARM SBCs, containers),
the function returns an empty string and type matching always fails.
